 <h1>To Robert Cary &amp; Company</h1>

<div class="docbody">
<div class="opener">
<table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		<td class="salutationLeft">Gentn</td>
		<td class="salutationRight">Williamsburg 1st May 1764.</td>
	      </tr>
      </table>
</div>
<p>The Copy of your Letter of the 13th of Februaryby Talmanis come to hand, but for want of the account Inclosed in the Original I am at a loss to conceive how my ballance can possibly be so much as 1811.1.1 in your favour, or Master Custiss so little as 1407.14.7 in his; however as the several accts will shew what Articles are charged and creditedwithout which there can be no judgingI shall postpone an explicit answer till they arrive.<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-07-02-0183-fn-0001" id="GEWN-02-07-02-0183-fn-0001-ptr">1</a></p>
<p>Your observations in regard to the money which Master Custis has in your hands are most certainly just, for his Acct and mine alth both under my directions, are become very distinct things since the Settlement of the Estate and on his behalf I now draw three Bills upon youtwo of them in favour of Fielding Lewis Esqr. for 100 &amp; 500 and the 3d in favour of Mr James Gibson for 200 makg in all 800 for which Sums your acct will have credit not doubting the due acceptance of the Bills.<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-07-02-0183-fn-0002" id="GEWN-02-07-02-0183-fn-0002-ptr">2</a></p>
<p>As to my own Debt I shall have no objections to allowing you Interest upon it untill it is discharged and you may charge it
<span class="pb" title="page number in print edition (no page scan available)" id="GEWN-02-07-02-pb-0306">[306]</span>
accordingly from this time forward, but had my Tobacco sold as I expected and the Bills been paid according to promise I was in hopes to have fallen very little in arrears; however as it is otherwise I shall endeavour to discharge the Balle as fast as I can, flattering myself there will be no just cause for complts of the Tobacco this year<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-07-02-0183-fn-0003" id="GEWN-02-07-02-0183-fn-0003-ptr">3</a>What little I make upon Potomackwhich indeed will not exceed 30 or 35 Hhdswill I hope be of a better quality than the last<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-07-02-0183-fn-0004" id="GEWN-02-07-02-0183-fn-0004-ptr">4</a>&amp; from this River (York) there remains 81 Hhds which I am told will proove good, 21 of which belongs to me and the other 60 to Master Custis<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-07-02-0183-fn-0005" id="GEWN-02-07-02-0183-fn-0005-ptr">5</a>of the 52 which went in Mathers 15 were mine &amp; 37 Master Custiss.<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-07-02-0183-fn-0006" id="GEWN-02-07-02-0183-fn-0006-ptr">6</a></p>
<p>I wish my fears may not proove true, but I am very apprehensive Boyes will stick long upon hand here, however what Tobacco I have both on this River &amp; Potomack shall be applied in loading of him<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-07-02-0183-fn-0007" id="GEWN-02-07-02-0183-fn-0007-ptr">7</a> and I wish a better dispatch to the Ship than many of your Corrispondants seem Inclined to give to it being, Yr Most Obedt Hble Servt</p>
<div class="closer">
<p class="signed">Go: Washington</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="docback">
<div class="note-source" id="GEWN-02-07-02-0183-sn">

   <p>
<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Autograph Letter Book ]">ALB</abbr>, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>.
</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-07-02-0183-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-02-07-02-0183-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>Carys letter of 13 Feb. 1764 has not been found, but see the invoice from Cary of that date. GW wrote Cary on 10 Aug. 1764 that he had received his account current from Cary, which has not been found. See his running account with Robert Cary &amp; Co. in <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Manuscript Ledger Book 1, 1750-72, in George Washington Papers, Library of Congress. ]">Ledger A</span>, 67, 198.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-07-02-0183-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-02-07-02-0183-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-07-02-0179&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-07-02-0179-fn-0003#GEWN-02-07-02-0179-fn-0003" class="document">Cash Accounts, April 1764, n.3.</a></p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-07-02-0183-fn-0003-ptr" id="GEWN-02-07-02-0183-fn-0003">3</a>

   <p>See GWs lengthy exposition of his financial relations with Cary in <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-07-02-0200-0001" class="document">his letter to Cary of 10 Aug. 1764</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-07-02-0183-fn-0004-ptr" id="GEWN-02-07-02-0183-fn-0004">4</a>

   <p>In July 1764 GW shipped twenty hogsheads of his Potomac tobacco to Cary aboard the <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">William and Mary</span>, John Boyes captain, and six more from Frederick County aboard the <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Polly Ogle</span> in October 1764 (see <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-07-02-0200-0001" class="document">GW to Cary, 10 Aug.</a> and <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-07-02-0207" class="document">8 Oct. 1764</a>, and <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Manuscript Ledger Book 1, 1750-72, in George Washington Papers, Library of Congress. ]">Ledger A</span>, 164). He received from Cary 135.18 for the twenty hogsheads in the <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">William and Mary</span> and 40.4.10 for the six in the <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Polly Ogle</span> (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Manuscript Ledger Book 1, 1750-72, in George Washington Papers, Library of Congress. ]">Ledger A</span>, 198).</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-07-02-0183-fn-0005-ptr" id="GEWN-02-07-02-0183-fn-0005">5</a>

   <p>GW received 291.4 sterling for the forty-one hogsheads of tobacco belonging to him shipped aboard the <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">William and Mary</span>, twenty-one of which were from his plantations in York and King William counties, the remainder from Fairfax and Frederick (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Manuscript Ledger Book 1, 1750-72, in George Washington Papers, Library of Congress. ]">Ledger A</span>, 16364, 198).</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-07-02-0183-fn-0006-ptr" id="GEWN-02-07-02-0183-fn-0006">6</a>

   <p>GW received 123.19 for the fifteen hogsheads of his own tobacco shipped in Captain Mathers <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">British King</span> (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Manuscript Ledger Book 1, 1750-72, in George Washington Papers, Library of Congress. ]">Ledger A</span>, 198).</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-07-02-0183-fn-0007-ptr" id="GEWN-02-07-02-0183-fn-0007">7</a>

   <p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-07-02-0183&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-07-02-0183-fn-0004#GEWN-02-07-02-0183-fn-0004" class="document">notes 4</a> and <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-07-02-0183&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-07-02-0183-fn-0005#GEWN-02-07-02-0183-fn-0005" class="document">5.</a></p>

</div>
